# Arithmetic Coding Algorithm in Pascal

Here's a complete implementation of the arithmetic coding algorithm in Pascal:

```pascal
program ArithmeticCoding;

uses
  crt;

type
  TProbability = array[0..255] of real;
  TCode = array[0..1000] of integer;

var
  text: string;
  freq: array[0..255] of integer;
  prob: TProbability;
  total: integer;
  low, high: real;
  code: TCode;
  codeLength: integer;

// Function to calculate character frequencies
procedure CalculateFrequencies(inputText: string);
var
  i: integer;
begin
  for i := 0 to 255 do
    freq[i] := 0;
  
  for i := 1 to length(inputText) do
    inc(freq[ord(inputText[i])]);
  
  total := 0;
  for i := 0 to 255 do
    total := total + freq[i];
end;

// Function to calculate probabilities
procedure CalculateProbabilities;
var
  i: integer;
  cumulative: real;
begin
  cumulative := 0;
  for i := 0 to 255 do
  begin
    if total > 0 then
      prob[i] := cumulative + (freq[i] / total)
    else
      prob[i] := 0;
    cumulative := prob[i];
  end;
end;

// Arithmetic encoding function
procedure Encode(inputText: string);
var
  i, j: integer;
  low, high, range: real;
  symbol: integer;
begin
  low := 0.0;
  high := 1.0;
  
  for i := 1 to length(inputText) do
  begin
    symbol := ord(inputText[i]);
    range := high - low;
    
    // Calculate new range
    if symbol = 0 then
      high := low + range * prob[0]
    else
      high := low + range * (prob[symbol] - prob[symbol-1]);
    
    low := low + range * prob[symbol-1];
    
    // Check for overflow
    if (low >= 0.5) or (high <= 0.5) then
    begin
      // Output bits
      if low >= 0.5 then
      begin
        code[codeLength] := 1;
        inc(codeLength);
        low := low - 0.5;
        high := high - 0.5;
      end
      else if high <= 0.5 then
      begin
        code[codeLength] := 0;
        inc(codeLength);
        low := low * 2;
        high := high * 2;
      end;
      
      // Normalize
      low := low * 2;
      high := high * 2;
    end;
  end;
  
  // Output remaining bits
  if low < 0.25 then
  begin
    code[codeLength] := 0;
    inc(codeLength);
  end
  else
  begin
    code[codeLength] := 1;
    inc(codeLength);
  end;
end;

// Arithmetic decoding function
function Decode(encodedCode: TCode; codeLength: integer; originalLength: integer): string;
var
  i, j: integer;
  low, high, range, value: real;
  symbol: integer;
  result: string;
begin
  low := 0.0;
  high := 1.0;
  result := '';
  
  // Calculate the encoded value
  value := 0.0;
  for i := 0 to codeLength - 1 do
  begin
    value := value + (encodedCode[i] * power(0.5, i + 1));
  end;
  
  // Decode
  for i := 1 to originalLength do
  begin
    range := high - low;
    // Find symbol
    symbol := 0;
    while (symbol < 256) and (low + range * prob[symbol] <= value) do
      inc(symbol);
    
    if symbol >= 256 then
      dec(symbol);
    
    // Update range
    if symbol = 0 then
      high := low + range * prob[0]
    else
      high := low + range * (prob[symbol] - prob[symbol-1]);
    
    low := low + range * prob[symbol-1];
    
    // Add decoded character
    result := result + chr(symbol);
  end;
  
  Decode := result;
end;

// Display the encoded binary code
procedure DisplayCode;
var
  i: integer;
begin
  writeln('Encoded binary code:');
  for i := 0 to codeLength - 1 do
    write(code[i]);
  writeln;
end;

// Main program
begin
  clrscr;
  
  writeln('Arithmetic Coding Algorithm Demo');
  writeln('================================');
  
  // Example text to encode
  text := 'ABRACADABRA';
  writeln('Original text: ', text);
  writeln;
  
  // Calculate frequencies and probabilities
  CalculateFrequencies(text);
  CalculateProbabilities;
  
  // Display probabilities
  writeln('Character probabilities:');
  for i := 0 to 255 do
  begin
    if freq[i] > 0 then
      writeln('Char ', chr(i), ': ', prob[i]:0:4, ' (frequency: ', freq[i], ')');
  end;
  writeln;
  
  // Reset code array
  codeLength := 0;
  for i := 0 to 1000 do
    code[i] := 0;
  
  // Encode the text
  Encode(text);
  
  // Display results
  DisplayCode;
  
  writeln;
  writeln('Encoding completed successfully!');
  
  // Pause to see results
  readln;
end.
```

## Key Features of this Implementation:

1. **Frequency Calculation**: Calculates character frequencies in the input text
2. **Probability Calculation**: Converts frequencies to probabilities
3. **Encoding**: Implements the core arithmetic coding algorithm
4. **Decoding**: Includes a basic decoding function (simplified for demonstration)
5. **Binary Output**: Shows the final binary representation

## How Arithmetic Coding Works:

1. **Model Creation**: Creates a probability model of characters
2. **Range Division**: Divides the unit interval [0,1) based on character probabilities
3. **Encoding**: Maps input symbols to subintervals
4. **Output**: Produces a single floating-point number as the encoded result
